{{Infobox philosopher |region = [[Western philosophy]] |era = [[Contemporary philosophy|21st-century philosophy]] |color = |image = |name = '''Fiona Jenkins''' |birth_date = |birth_place = |death_date = |death_place = |school_tradition = [[Continental philosophy|Continental]] | institutions = [[Australian National University]] |main_interests = Feminist Theory, Cultural Theory, Screen And Media Culture, Poststructuralism, Social Philosophy | thesis_title = Becoming What We Are: A Study of Revaluation, Realism and Self-Representation in Nietzsche's Writings | thesis_url = https://ora.ox.ac.uk/objects/uuid:d8a52465-f3c0-44e1-a325-73c7934f39c8 | thesis_year = 1996 | doctoral_advisor = [[Bernard Williams]] and [[Alan Montefiore]] | doctoral_students = |notable_ideas = | spouse = | education = [[Balliol College, Oxford]] (PhD), [[Sussex University]] (MA) |influences = [[Nietzsche]], [[Wittgenstein]], [[Derrida]], [[Judith Butler]], [[Jean-Luc Nancy]] |awards = |website = https://researchers.anu.edu.au/researchers/jenkins-fk?term=fiona%20jenkins }}
'''Fiona Jenkins''' is an Australian philosopher and Associate Professor of [[Philosophy]] at the [[Australian National University]]. She is known for her works on [[feminist theory]], [[the status of women in philosophy]] and [[Nietzschean philosophy]]. Jenkins was the convenor of the ANU Gender Institute from 2012 to 2015.<ref>{{cite web |title=Fiona Jenkins – Gender Equality in Higher Education 2018 |url=https://genderequalityconference2018.com/event_speakers/fiona-jenkins/ |website=genderequalityconference2018.com |accessdate=7 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Knierim |first1=Kristian |title=Prof. Fiona Jenkins |url=https://www.sowi.rub.de/jahoda/profs/w2017_18_jenkins.html.en |website=www.sowi.rub.de |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=O'Connor |first1=Peg |title=Review of Women in Philosophy: What Needs to Change? |journal=[[Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews]] |date=28 April 2014 |url=https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/women-in-philosophy-what-needs-to-change/ |accessdate=7 August 2018 |issn=1538-1617}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Merlino |first1=Anthony |title=Stifled Voices: Women in Philosophy Through the Eyes of Fiona Jenkins |journal=[[Woroni]] |date=2017 |url=https://www.woroni.com.au/words/stifled-voices-women-in-philosophy-through-the-eyes-of-fiona-jenkins/ |accessdate=7 August 2018 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Duffy |first1=Leigh |title=Katrina Hutchison and Fiona Jenkins (eds.), Women in Philosophy: What Needs to Change? |journal=[[The Journal of Value Inquiry]] |date=17 January 2015 |volume=50 |issue=2 |pages=495–500 |doi=10.1007/s10790-015-9481-1 |url=https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10790-015-9481-1 |accessdate=7 August 2018 |language=en |issn=0022-5363}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Leuschner |first1=Anna |title=Katrina Hutchison and Fiona Jenkins (eds): Women in Philosophy: What Needs to Change? |journal=[[Journal for General Philosophy of Science]] |date=20 December 2014 |volume=46 |issue=1 |pages=245–249 |doi=10.1007/s10838-014-9282-4 |url=https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10838-014-9282-4 |accessdate=7 August 2018 |language=en |issn=0925-4560}}</ref>
