'''Mohamed Hamouda Hamouda Bensaï''' (1902 in Batna – 1998 in Algiers) was an Algerian philosopher and essayist. He studied philosophy at [[Sorbonne]], and was one of the major Algerian thinkers<ref name="Duthel2015">{{cite book|last=Duthel|first=Heinz|title=La Legion et la bataille a Ðiên Biên Phú|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XOnVBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA218|date=26 February 2015|publisher=BoD – Books on Demand|isbn=978-3-7347-6596-4|page=218|language=French}}</ref> from the 1930s onwards. He chaired the circle of the Association of Franco-North Africa, founded by [[Marcellin Piel]].

