'''Pierre Louis Parisis''' (17 August 1795 &ndash; 1866) was the [[Roman Catholic]] bishop of the [[Bishopric of Langres]] in [[Haute-Marne]], [[France]], from 1835 to 1851.<ref>{{CathEncy|wstitle=Langres}}</ref>

In 1847 he formed the ''Archconfraternity of Reparation for blasphemy and the neglect of Sunday'' to promote [[Acts of Reparation to Jesus Christ]].<ref>{{CathEncy|wstitle=Reparation}}</ref> He is also noted for his efforts within the Assembly of 1848 for establishing the ecclesiastical college of St. Dizier and for his discussions concerning the educational reforms. He was a member of the commission which prepared the draft project for the [[Falloux Laws]] increasing the Catholic clergy's influence in French education.

